For reasons unexplained, observations from the field,during and after measurement, differ from files viewed and processed in the office.  Values for Q were manually recorded in the field with no post processing. These Q values were consistant and no issues werer apparant. Once back in the office discharge files were loaded for processing and calculated Q's were found to be inconsistant with field observations. Std deviation in the field after all transects were collected was 1.34. With post processing files in the office the best Std. deviation that could be obtained was 3.33. Recommend confidence be placed in the field observations.
